  <body>
    <segment id="1">

Political signal</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="23" relname="span">

Currently, the parties are determining who they will send into the race in the constituencies of the region for the 2002 federal election.</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="20" relname="span">  

This happens rather incidentally,</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="3" relname="elaboration"> 

at least without the involvement of a broad public.</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="21" relname="cause">  

The residents of cities and municipalities usually only find out shortly before the decision on the federal level who their direct political contact in Berlin could be.</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="7" relname="reason"> 

By then, it is often too late to determine the key issues of the candidates.</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="21" relname="span"> 

The positions they take on specific local issues remain unknown to many voters at first.</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="19" relname="span">

Therefore, it makes sense to familiarize oneself early on with the ideas of the candidates for the Bundestag.</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="18" relname="span">  

In some cases, their influence at the highest level is important.</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="17" relname="span"> 

This is particularly true for projects that the federal government is promoting in the regions,</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="16" relname="span"> 

such as bypass roads and the traffic project Deutsche Einheit Nr. 17 - the expansion of the Havel.</segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="25" relname="span">  

The latter is controversial in the outskirts of Potsdam.</segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="15" relname="joint"> 

It can be said without exaggeration that the opponents of the project are clearly in the majority.</segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="15" relname="joint">  

For them, the stance of the candidates in the constituency on this issue must also be a political signal.</segment>
<group id="17" type="span" parent="9" relname="elaboration" />
